Three critically injured in French gas explosion 
Three people were critically ill in hospital with extensive burns and
lung injuries after a gas explosion in France's second city Lyon,
hospital sources said on Friday.
One of the three, a 28-year-old man had burns over 97 percent of his
body and his condition was described as "desperate". His female
companion was badly burned on her face and hands in the explosion which
occurred in the small hours and set off a fire in a seven-storey
apartment building. Both were in intensive care.
Another woman was also described as critically ill with burns over 50
percent of her body and severe lung injuries.
